      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p>The papers of Harold Gould Henderson, author and professor of Japanese art and
               culture, were given to the Library of Congress by his wife, Mary Benjamin Henderson,
               in 1985 and 1991. </p>
      </acqinfo>
